(300,E'#RecommenderHelpTitle',E'default',E'How to recommend a preprint'),
(301,E'#RecommenderHelpInfo',E'default',E'####**As a member of *{{appname}}*, you can recommend preprints**, i.e. articles not yet peer-reviewed and not yet published in scientific journals.\n&nbsp;\n\n<img alt="Preprints" src="../static/images/workflow3.png" width="900" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n\n###Before recommending a preprint \n\n1. You **must be sure that the preprint you have selected is remarkable**. Start a recommendation process only if you are highly motivated to do so and if the preprint has strong qualities: crucial, original or previously untested hypotheses, scientific rigor, refinement of the demonstration, outstanding quality of the data and methodology, noteworthy scientific consequences, etc.\n2. You **must be sure that you have no conflict of interest** of any kind with the content or with the authors of the preprint, and that you are not recommending a preprint from close colleagues, recent co-authors, relatives or friends.\n3. You must agree to comply with the [code of conduct of {{appname}}](../about/ethics).\n&nbsp;\n\n     You can then start the recommendation process for this preprint by clicking on the green button at the end of this page. \n&nbsp;\n\n\n###Details about the recommendation process\n\n1. You read the preprint and you find it particularly interesting. You decide to initiate the recommendation process and become the “recommender” of the preprint.\n\n2. You must obtain (through the website) at least two high-quality reviews. You can be one of the reviewers so you have to find at least one additional reviewer within or outside {{appname}}, selected on the basis of his/her expertise. You must continue to solicit reviews until you obtain at least two high-quality reviews, which may or may not include your own. Reviewers can choose to disclose their identity (preferred) or to remain anonymous.\n\n3. Once you have obtained the necessary reviews, you can write and send your decision to the authors of the preprint, together with the reviews, via the website. You may 1) accept the article and write your recommendation, 2) ask the authors for modifications or 3) reject the article. If the authors modify their article, they must deposit a new version of the article in the preprint server and obtain a DOI for this new version. You then write a short text of recommendation explaining the recommendation, when all the requested modifications have been made\n\n4. The recommendation text signed by you, all reviews (anonymous or otherwise), and all correspondence with the authors are sent to the Managing Board of {{appname}}. Before sending their recommendations and reviews, all recommenders and reviewers must declare that they have no conflict of interest of any kind with the content or the authors of the article, and that they are not recommending or reviewing an article published by close colleagues, recent co-authors, relatives or friends. The Managing Board will carry out a quality control check on the format and the deontology of reviews and recommendations.\n\n5. The recommendation text signed by you, all reviews (anonymous or otherwise), and all correspondence with the authors are posted on the {{appname}} website. The recommendation is widely publicized in media and social networks, and becomes a citable reference.'),
