(347,E'#RecommenderEditDecisionText',E'default',E'For a first round of review, you must obtain at least two reviews of high quality. \n\n* __Recommend the article__ only if the preprint can now serve as reference in the scientific literature.  \n* __Ask for a revision__ if you think the process can eventually lead to a recommendation but the preprint needs improvements to attain this point.   \n* __Reject this article__ if you think that no amelioration can lead to a recommendation.   \n \n__In case you recommend the article__: \nYou have to write a so-called **Recommendation text** that will have a DOI and will be published. It should have a nice title, contain between about 300 to 1500 words, describe the context and explain why the article is worth a recommendation. Limits of the article can also be discussed. This text also contains references (at least that of the article).'),
(348,E'#RecommenderEditDecision',E'default',NULL),
(349,E'#RecommenderEditDecisionTitle',E'default',E'Decision'),
(350,E'#ConflictsForReviewers',E'default',E'<font style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2em;">  \n<div style="text-align:left">Notably, I should not review articles written by close colleagues (with whom I have published in the last four years, with whom I have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom I am currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal), or written by authors whom I know evaluated - as recommender or reviewer - one or more of my own articles in the last four years, or written by family members, friends, or anyone for whom bias might affect the nature of my review - see the <a href="../about/ethics" title="code of ethical conduct">code of conduct</a></div>  \n</font>'),
(351,E'#ConflictsForRecommenders',E'default',E'<font style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.2em;">  \n<div style="text-align:left">I should not handle articles written by close colleagues (with whom I have published in the last four years, with whom I have received joint funding in the last four years, or with whom I am currently writing a manuscript, or submitting a grant proposal), or written by authors whom I know evaluated - as recommender or reviewer - one or more of my own articles in the last four years, or written by family members, friends, or anyone for whom bias might affect the nature of my evaluation. See the <a href="../about/ethics">code of conduct</a></div>  \n</font>'),
